00:13:57.419 --> 00:14:04.000
ownership of this pipeline. Again, moving it from the head of one person into a replicable

00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:08.140
example that's well-documented.

00:14:08.140 --> 00:14:15.500
I think we started with something like this. It works. The concept is great, and there's

00:14:15.500 --> 00:14:24.659
good bones here. But if we want to scale it and we want to bring it into 2025, we ended

00:14:24.659 --> 00:14:29.700
up making something like this, where the idea is multiple chefs or cooks can interact with

00:14:29.700 --> 00:14:36.859
a recipe that's well-documented and replicable. We employed some automation here in the form

